The paper deals with speaker recognition systems and the main issue is compensating the discrepancy between different languages. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SD (Sound). The paper also mentions using state-of-the-art techniques as backend, which suggests the involvement of machine learning and natural language processing, making cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.LG (Learning) likely sub-categories as well. Additionally, the paper mentions unique methods such as unsupervised language clustering and inter language variability compensation, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper deals with signal processing, which could also fall under cs.SD.
